In declarative approach we put all the details in yaml document and we pass it on to kuberntes cluster , Cluser takes care 
of creating the resources accourdingly.

# kubectl run nginx --image='nginx:latest' --port=80 --dry-run=client -o yaml> ngix-pod.yaml
To expose the port 
# kubectl expose pod nginx-svc --port=80 --type=NodePort --dry-run=client -o yaml > nginx-svc.yaml

In nginx-pod.yaml the lables should math the slector in nginx-svc.yaml 

Here the "label: Name-badge" assinged to pod and selector in service, filter the name-badge and identify the correct resource to sent the traffic , This is how the pod and services communicae with eath other

The above command will create yaml file with specified configuration after that it commnicae with with other 

